 ---
  Build Tally integration in accobot-app.

  Stack: Laravel 13, Vue 3, Inertia.js, Tailwind CSS (violet-* only, never indigo-*), PostgreSQL. Multi-tenant via BelongsToTenant trait — always
  withoutGlobalScope('tenant') in API controllers. Permissions: integrations.view / integrations.manage. Flash via page.props.flash.success / page.props.flash.error.

  ---
  Architecture

  Tally is the source of truth. Accobot replicates the cloud-tally.in connector API so Tally's connector talks directly to Accobot. Three flows — all initiated by the
  connector, never by Accobot:

  1. Inbound: Connector POSTs Tally data to Accobot. AlterID unchanged → skip. Action: Delete → is_active = false. Tally always wins.
  2. Outbound GET: Connector GETs Accobot-originated records (Swagger paths). Tally reads and syncs.
  3. Confirmation POST: Tally sends back TallyId after creating Accobot-originated records (Swagger paths).

  Accobot makes zero outbound HTTP calls to Tally.

  ---
  Authentication

  Accobot generates per-tenant inbound_token (48-char, auto-generated on TallyConnection::creating()). Token is in $hidden. Tenant enters company_id (Tally company UUID) in
   Accobot settings. Tenant copies base_url (url('/')), token, and company_id into Tally connector. All connector requests send Authorization: Bearer {inbound_token}.
  Accobot resolves tenant from token via withoutGlobalScope('tenant'). Returns 401 if missing or inactive. No Sanctum on Tally API routes.

