  Body: { "Data": [{ "Id": accobot_tally_table_id, "TallyId": "string", "IsSynced": true }] }. Store TallyId. Set is_synced = true on mapped Accobot model
  (client/vendor/product/invoice).

  ---
  Service Layer

  app/Services/Tally/TallyInboundSync.php

  syncLedgerGroups(TallyConnection $conn, array $items): TallySyncLog
  syncLedgers(TallyConnection $conn, array $items, bool $fullSync = false): TallySyncLog
  syncStockItems(TallyConnection $conn, array $items, bool $fullSync = false): TallySyncLog
  syncStockGroups(TallyConnection $conn, array $items): TallySyncLog
  syncStockCategories(TallyConnection $conn, array $items): TallySyncLog
  syncVouchers(TallyConnection $conn, array $items, string $type, bool $fullSync = false): TallySyncLog

  Each method: create log → strip \u0004 → loop items → check AlterID → upsert → auto-map → mark log done.

  syncLedgers auto-map: derive ledger_category, if customer → Client::updateOrCreate(['tally_ledger_id' => $ledger->id], [...fields]), if vendor →
  Vendor::updateOrCreate(...).

  syncStockItems auto-map: Product::updateOrCreate(['tally_stock_item_id' => $item->id], [...fields]).

  syncVouchers: upsert tally_vouchers → delete + re-insert tally_voucher_inventory_entries and tally_voucher_ledger_entries → if type = Sales:
  Invoice::updateOrCreate(['tally_voucher_id' => $voucher->id], [...fields]).

  app/Services/Tally/TallyReportSync.php

  syncReport(TallyConnection $conn, string $type, array $payload): TallySyncLog

  Inserts a new tally_reports row. Never updates — keeps full history of snapshots.

  app/Services/Tally/TallyOutboundFormatter.php

  formatLedgerGroups(Collection $groups): array
  formatLedgers(Collection $ledgers): array
  formatStockItems(Collection $items): array
  formatStockGroups(Collection $groups): array
  formatStockCategories(Collection $cats): array
  formatSalesVouchers(Collection $vouchers): array
  formatPurchaseVouchers(Collection $vouchers): array
  formatDebitNoteVouchers(Collection $vouchers): array
  formatCreditNoteVouchers(Collection $vouchers): array

  Each method returns array in exact Tally payload structure (field names, casing, \u0004 prefix on system units).

